lines.text: it's not how fast you can go
the force goes into the flow
if you pick up the beat
you can forget about the heat
more that just a dotted line more than just a dash
it's a test of ultimate will
you've got to pick up the pace
if you want to stay in the race
more than a finish line must feed this burning need
something always fires the light that get's in your eyes
that flashed & fades in the summer sky
you can rest at the side of the road
if you can miss a stride
but nobody gets a free ride
more than just the bottom line or a lucky shot in the dark
something always fires the light that get's in your eyes
that flashes & fades in the summer sky
you can do a lot in a lifetime
if you don't burn out too fast
you can make the most of the distance
something always fires the light that get's in your eyes
that flashes & fades in the summer sky
something always fires the light that get's in your eyes
that flashes & fades in the summer sky
